## Errors & Mistakes (read these)
1. SILENT CACHE BUG via functools.wraps omission: the caching middleware
   namespaces cache keys by func.__name__; the coercion wrapper was named
   "wrapper", so obj_read entries were cached under "wrapper_..." and the
   "obj_read_..." invalidation prefixes never matched -> stale tag/alias
   reads with NO error. @functools.wraps(attr) is load-bearing, not hygiene.
2. Mixed response identity: cache MISS returned the inner server's family,
   HIT returned the SDK family -> equality tests caught it. The middleware
   now normalizes results to its declared response type (no-op in production
   where the binding already returns SDK models).
3. `uv sync --group dev` (run for prek) PRUNES the test group and corrupted a
   full-suite run mid-flight (76 bogus failures incl. missing moviepy);
   re-sync --group test before pytest. This bit twice this session.
4. tests/flow/test_evaluation_imperative.py passed tsi ObjectVersionFilter
   into client._objects -> pydantic rejects foreign models; per the user
   directive the TEST now constructs the SDK model (client-API tests use the
   client's currency).
5. zsh mangles `git show $SRC:path` ($SRC:w parsed as modifier) — quote it.

